  "prompt": "Do I have to shave during a passport appointment?",
  "response": "There is no specific requirement for you to shave before attending a passport appointment. However, there are guidelines regarding how your appearance should be for your passport photo, which is a critical part of the application process. \n\nThe key is that your passport photo should accurately represent how you look most of the time. If having facial hair is your usual appearance, you don't need to shave it off for the photo. The most important thing is that the photo clearly shows your facial features, so avoid any hairstyles or accessories that could obscure your face.\n\nIf you are taking a new photo at the appointment, ensure you follow any specific guidelines provided by the passport office regarding photo requirements, including size, background, and expression. If you're unsure, it might be a good idea to contact the passport office or check their website for detailed instructions.",
